# Secrets — credentials, signing material, API keys.
# Keep this list aggressive; better to false-positive than to ever leak.
*.env
.env
.env.*
!.env.example
*.pem
*.p12
*.p8
*.cer
*.cert
*.crt
*.key
*.pfx
*.mobileprovision
*.provisionprofile
secrets/
.secrets/
secrets.*
credentials.*
GoogleService-Info.plist
AuthKey_*.p8

# User data — workspace files should never be in the repo. The real
# database lives in the user's container or iCloud Drive folder; if a
# stray copy lands here it's accidental and shouldn't be committed.
# Patterns anchored to repo root so they only catch stray user-data
# folders, not source-code directories of the same name (we have a
# Keystone/Features/Assets/ that *is* code).
*.sqlite
*.sqlite-wal
*.sqlite-shm
/Assets/
/Inbox/
# Personal source documents staged at the project root for dev/test
# imports (e.g. a vehicle-records folder). Private papers shouldn't be
# checked in even if a contributor leaves them lying around.
/Cars/

# Logs
*.log

# Instruments / profiling output. Traces routinely land in `.traces/`
# (via `bin/profile-gallery.sh`) or at the repo root with the
# `Launch_<App>_<timestamp>_<uuid>.trace` naming pattern that
# Instruments.app uses. Both can be hundreds of MB and shouldn't be
# checked in.
.traces/
Launch_*.trace/

# Claude scratch (in case anything ever lands inside the repo)
.claude/
CLAUDE.local.md
